===Noun===
'''ball''' (''plural'' [[balls]])

#A solid or hollow [[sphere]].
#An object, generally spherical, used for playing games.
#(''baseball'') A pitch that falls outside the strike zone.
#(''pinball'') An opportunity to launch the ball into play.
#(''ballistics'') A solid non-explosive missile for a cannon etc.
#(''mathematics'') The set of points in a [[metric space]] lying within a given distance (the [[radius]]) of a given point; specifically, the [[homologue]] of the [[disk]] in a [[Euclidean space]] of any number of [[dimension]]s.
#(''mildly vulgar slang''; ''usually in plural'') A [[testicle]]
#:- see [[WikiSaurus:testicles]].
#(''in plural''; ''mildly vulgar slang'') [[Nonsense]].
#:''That's a load of balls, and you know it!'' - Synonyms - See [[WikiSaurus:Nonsense]]
#A formal dance.
#(''colloquial'') A very enjoyable time.
#:''I had a ball at that concert''
#In [[cricket]], a single [[delivery]] by the [[bowler]], six of which make up an [[over]]


====Synonyms====
*(''testicle''): [[bollock]] (''vulgar''), [[nut]] (''mildly vulgar'') 
